    <div id='ofis_welcome_container'>
        <div id='welcome_header'>
            <div class='green_box'></div>
            <h1 class='green'>Welcome to OFIS</h1>
            <div class='clear_float'></div>
        </div>
        <div id='welcome_body'>
            <div class='welcome_post_container'><h3>From The OFIS Office</h3><p><strong><span style="color: #ff6600;">The OFIS Office will be CLOSED from Friday March 11 to Monday March 28 for staff vacations during Spring Break - Email will be monitored for emergent situations and registration for OFIS PD events is available throughout this time period</span></strong>

<strong><span style="color: #008000;">OFIS Office Hours - Monday to Friday from 9am to 4pm - Our staff are often out of the office working with members. Messages can be left by both voicemail and email which are monitored regularly and returned within 48 hours of receipt.
</span></strong>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;</p></div><div class='welcome_post_container'><h3>What is OFIS?</h3><p><strong>OFIS is the largest, fastest growing, most diverse independent school association. We exist to:</strong>
<ul>
	<li><span style="color: #006633;"><em>connect </em> independent schools in a network that shares resources, provides professional development for school leaders, offers administrative and policy support</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #006633;"><em>advocate </em> for access to government education resources making them available to independent schools</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #006633;"><em>protect and support </em>true parental choice in education by providing public information and ensuring independent schools’ right to reasonable self-definition</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #006633;">encourage greater <em>public awareness and appreciation </em>for independent schools’ contributions to the provincial educational landscape by promoting standard-setting leadership in member schools</span></li>
</ul></p></div>        </div>
    </div>
</div>
